HANTAVIRUS UPDATE 2008 - AMERICAS (14): USA (WASHINGTON)
********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon 18 Aug 2008
Source: Yakima Herald-Republic [edited]
<http://www.yakima-herald.com/stories/6845>


An Ellensburg police officer died Friday [15 Aug 2008] from what is
believed to have been a deadly hantavirus [infection], a rare illness
contracted from inhaling airborne urine and feces of mice.

The policeman, [age] 34, died at Yakima Valley Memorial Hospital at
approximately 2 pm, barely 48 hours after suffering symptoms. Victims
of a hantavirus [infection may] suffer flu-like symptoms and die of
suffocation.

Police said it's unknown at this time when or exactly where the
officer contracted the rare, but often fatal disease. Public health
officials are said to be investigating.

[Byline: Leah Beth Ward]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The specific hantavirus involved in this case is not stated, but
most likely is Sin Nombre virus.

A map showing the location of Yakima in south-central Washington can
be accessed at
<http://www.gonorthwest.com/washington/washington-state-map.htm>. - Mod.TY]
